ferc_filing_data.tariff_title: Market-Based Rate Tariff FERC Electric Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Applicability: This schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by PSE&G not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of PSE&G.
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by mutual agreement between the purchaser and PSE&G.
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Availability: Public Service Electric and Gas Company (PSE&G) makes electric capacity available under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale.
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Seller Category. Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast region and a Category 1 seller in the Central, Southwest Power Pool, Southeast, Southwest and Northwest regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a).
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text:

record_data.record_plain_text: Separately Stated Prices. The prices for wholesale generation of electricity, transmission services and ancillary services shall be separately stated from any sale made under this Rate Schedule.
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Compliance with Commission Regulations. PSE&G shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning PSE&G???s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes PSE&G to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the PSE&G???s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning PSE&G???s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by mutual agreement between the purchaser and PSE&G.
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Effective Date: This Rate Schedule shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (???Commission???).
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text:
Ancillary Services: PSE&G makes ancillary services available under this Tariff as specified below:
PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
record_data.filing_title: Compliance Filing of PSE&G Market-Based Rate Tariff Volume No. 6

record_data.record_plain_text: Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. PSE&G???s market-based rate authority is not subject to any limitations. PSE&G???s market-based rate authority is not subject to any exemptions, waivers or blanket authorizations. Exemptions granted in Public Service Electric and Gas Company, et al., 134 FERC ?? 61,138 (2011): Waiver of the affiliate restrictions codified in the Commission???s regulations at 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.39.
